headline: How The State Street (STT) Narrative Is Shifting On Capital Markets Hopes And Execution Risks
summary: State Street’s fair value estimate has been adjusted from US$143.60 to US$144.30, a small move that still puts the spotlight on how analysts are rethinking the stock. Behind that tweak, you are seeing a clear split in research views, with some firms lifting price targets toward levels like US$144 and US$155, while others trim theirs by US$2 to US$4 as they weigh Capital Markets potential against execution and macro risks. Read on to see what is driving these calls and how you can keep up with...
